<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[192,1440,1377,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,336,1377,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Rounded punctures along elytral suture distinguish this species from both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fleutiaux Pronotum" authorityYear="1929" box="[1287,1440,1378,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Phlegon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis box="[1287,1440,1378,1401]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Otto" authorityYear="2017" box="[245,436,1410,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Phlegon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiriquiensis">
<emphasis box="[245,436,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. chiriquiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Males are distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[920,1101,1410,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Euryptychus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herculeanus">
<emphasis box="[920,1101,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. herculeanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shorter antennomere IX in relation to X; subequal in both segments for 
<taxonomicName box="[780,963,1442,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Euryptychus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herculeanus">
<emphasis box="[780,963,1442,1466]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. herculeanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Males are further distinguished from male 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Otto" authorityYear="2017" box="[259,437,1474,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Phlegon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis box="[259,437,1474,1497]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shorter, thicker antennal rami on antennomeres IX–X; elongate and thinner in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Otto" authorityYear="2017" box="[192,371,1506,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Phlegon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis box="[192,371,1506,1529]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laporte. One" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName=", Laporte, Det. R. L. Otto" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[523,647,1506,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Phlegon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buqueti">
<emphasis box="[523,647,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. buqueti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Otto" authorityYear="2017" box="[1039,1218,1506,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Phlegon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis box="[1039,1218,1506,1529]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by relative length of antennomere IX in relation to X: IX longer than X in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laporte. One" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName=", Laporte, Det. R. L. Otto" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[858,981,1538,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Phlegon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buqueti">
<emphasis box="[858,981,1538,1562]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. buqueti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and IX as long as X in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Otto" authorityYear="2017" box="[1255,1433,1538,1561]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Phlegon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="panamensis">
<emphasis box="[1255,1433,1538,1561]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. panamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Females are further distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[776,955,1570,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Euryptychus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herculeanus">
<emphasis box="[776,955,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. herculeanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by shape of antennomeres IX–X: simply serrate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laporte. One" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName=", Laporte, Det. R. L. Otto" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[319,444,1602,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Phlegon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buqueti">
<emphasis box="[319,444,1602,1626]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. buqueti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and asymmetrically serrate in 
<taxonomicName box="[831,1013,1602,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Eucnemidae" genus="Euryptychus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="herculeanus">
<emphasis box="[831,1013,1602,1626]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">P. herculeanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
